          "Expand and simplify: $x^2 + x^2 - 14x + 49 = 169 \\Rightarrow 2x^2 - 14x - 120 = 0$.",
          "Divide by 2: $x^2 - 7x - 60 = 0$. Factorize: $(x-12)(x+5) = 0$. Base must be positive, so $x=12$."
        ],
        "derivation": "x^2 + (x-7)^2 = 13^2 \\\\ 2x^2 - 14x + 49 - 169 = 0 \\\\ 2x^2 - 14x - 120 = 0 \\\\ x^2 - 7x - 60 = 0 \\\\ (x-12)(x+5) = 0"
